cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.SY, cs.SD, cs.LG 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper discusses a neural network based text-to-speech/speech synthesis pipeline, which falls under the domain of natural language processing. 
- cs.SD (Sound): The paper deals with generating audio output from text input, which falls under the domain of sound. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes modifications to existing Seq2seq architectures to improve training time and reduce model complexity, which falls under the domain of system optimization. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper discusses the use of neural networks for text-to-speech/speech synthesis, which falls under the domain of machine learning. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision): Although the paper does not directly deal with computer vision, some of the techniques used in the proposed model, such as attention alignment, are commonly used in computer vision tasks.
